news.title: Nashik civic body likely to revise property tax for industries
news.para: According to AIMA, the property tax has been increased manifold for the industries in the past three-four years.

news.title: Chandigarh administration pushes for conversion of leasehold properties
news.para: UT adviser Dharam Pal on Thursday met the MHA officers. The administration had recently also written a letter to the MHA for giving in-principle nod for conversion of leasehold properties.

news.title: Mysuru: Muda cites soaring price of land for its inability to develop new layouts
news.para: Consequently, Muda is unable to allot sites to new applicants, and for the past decade, has been pushing for the adoption of a 50-50 site-sharing formula with farmers parting with their land for the layouts.

news.title: Ahmedabad: Vejalpur society gets HC nod for redevelopment
news.para: Justice Sangeeta Vishen permitted Swami Vivekanandnagar Cooperative Housing Society to go for demolition of existing 11 blocks and construction of new buildings for 78 flat owners, out of whom 74 (93.5%) consented for redevelopment.

news.title: Regularisation of 24 colonies to be tabled in Gurugram civic body's house meet
news.para: ​The biggest of these 24 illegal colonies is New Palam Vihar Colony Pocket 1 and 2 which is spread across 525.3 acres in Choma, Sarai Alawari and Pawala Khusurpur. TOI had reported on June 14 that MCG has received a list of 24 colonies from the department of urban local bodies (ULB) to be considered for regularisation.

news.title: Gurugram: DTCP serves notice to Sabyasachi Infrastructure over illegal colony
news.para: On the basis of complaints filed by investors, the department carried out an investigation and found that Sabyasachi Infrastructure is developing a residential licensed plotted colony under the Deen Dayal Jan Aawas Yojna in Sector 3 of Farrukhnagar.

news.title: NCDRC orders M3M to stop the construction of 'illegal tower' in Gurugram
news.para: A complaint was filed by around 300 homebuyers with NCDRC. The complaint was filed by those that were allocated homes in the first 10 approved towers.

news.title: Nine real estate firms under CBI scanner for 'diversion' of Rs 14,683 crore DHFL funds
news.para: The outstanding amount towards Creatoz Builders is Rs 1,192 crore, towards Township Developers Rs 6,002 crore, towards Shishir Realty Rs 1,233 crore and towards Sunlink Real Estate Private Limited Rs 2,185 crore, the officials said.

news.title: ED attaches Unitech assets worth Rs 257 crore in a money-laundering case
news.para: The agency said its probe has found that homebuyers' funds amounting to Rs 244 crore were "illegally diverted" by Unitech promoters Ajay and Sanjay Chandra to CIG Realty Fund.

news.title: Cement carbon dioxide emissions quietly double in 20 years
news.para: In 2021, worldwide emissions from making cement for buildings, roads and other infrastructure hit nearly 2.9 billion tons (2.6 billion metric tons) of carbon dioxide, which is more than 7% of the global carbon emissions.

news.title: ANZ Bengaluru leases six lakh sq ft from Embassy Group in Bengaluru
news.para: The new facility, currently under construction, is designed to accommodate over 6,000 employees.

news.title: Aswani Promoters inks pact for 2.2-million-sq-ft mixed-use development in Pune
news.para: In a separate development, another Pune-Based real estate developer raised Rs 130 crores for its premium residential project. The funds have been raised for a premium residential complex spread across around half a million sq ft.

news.title: Row over move to raise luxury tax of buildings along Kochi metro line
news.para: The revenue department has initiated steps to assess the residential buildings on both sides of the Metro line from Aluva to SN Junction.

news.title: Gujarat government approves project in private residential societies through public partnership
news.para: The government has allotted the fund to carry out various works in residential private societies through public partnership.

news.title: Ashiana Housing & Lohia Jain Group join hands to develop residential project in Pune
news.para: Spread over 11.33 acres, the project will be developed by Ashiana Housing and will offer a total of 990 residential units. Phase I of the project will comprise 224 units.
